title: Games Of The Week In New Jersey
text: Games Of The Week In New Jersey Pat PJR Rice Talk about it in the njvarsity Message Boards Williamstown (4-0) at Cherokee (2-1), Friday night. One of the top public school matchups in New Jersey, with Cherokee winning South Jersey Group 5 the last two years and Williamstown in 2012. Williamstown has posted shutouts in their last two games and OLB Tyrick Glenn and DE Eric Smith are among those making plays. Cherokee has QB/OLB Evan Powell and RB/DB Jon Lovatt leading them and are coming off a bye. Jackson (3-1) at Toms River North (3-1), Friday night. Jackson is coming off a tough, 2-0 loss to Brick. The Jaguars have allowed 12 points in their four games, including last week's losing safety. They have received good quarterback play from Danny Barker, while Austin Ostrander supplies good two way play on the line. Toms River North can put up points and feature QB Mike Husni and WR Darrion Carrington. Ramapo (3-1) at Wayne Hills (4-1), Friday night. This is a big rivalry game and the winner is in good shape for the playoffs. Ramapo's only loss was a heartbreaker to Old Tappan. They're led by QB Keith Woetzel and RB/DB Joe O'Hagan. Wayne Hills lost their first last week to Pascack Valley in a close one. LB/TE Joe Kenny is a man among boys, while the passing of Brandon DeVera has opened a new dimension to the offense. Bridgewater-Raritan (4-0) at Elizabeth (4-0), Friday night. Two undefeated teams in the Mid-State 38 square off. Elizabeth features WR Jahmin Muse, who has been filling in at quarterback for the injured Jaquill Burch. One player to watch is two way lineman Wakeem Brooks. The Minutemen have been in some close games, keeping things close to the vest. Bridgewater-Raritan features QB Eric Nickel, who can run and pass. They also have a good defense, getting good play from LB Mike Celli and DL Matt Alesandro. Red Bank (4-0) at Raritan (3-0), Friday night. Red Bank has an experienced team and a defense that's allowed 20 points. Their offense features WR Sadiq Palmer and OL Ricky Wild leads is part of an experienced line. Raritan outscored three quality programs in Manasquan, Matawan, and Freehold Boro, 100-17. Their offense revolves around RB Derek Ernst and Bo Bentley is one of the guys blocking up front. Hanover Park (4-0) at Lenape Valley (4-0), Friday night. Hanover Park has outscored the opposition, 160-22 and had three touchdowns each from RB Rory DeLuca and QB Donato Casolaro. Hanover Park has not been challenged yet, while Lenape Valley has been in competitive games. Lenape Valley has outscored opponents, 100-49, and feature the running of Steve Leyden and the two way line play of Rich Fritzky.
